<emphasis box="[151,341,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Gagea fragifera</emphasis>
(Vill.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer, E. &amp; Lopez Gonzalez, G." box="[429,761,652,678]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="643 - 645" refId="ref8785" refString="Bayer, E. &amp; Lopez Gonzalez, G. (1989) Nomenclatural notes on some names in Gagea Salisb. (Liliaceae). Taxon 38: 643 - 645." type="journal article" year="1989">Bayer &amp; LÃ³pez (1989: 663)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, 
<treatmentCitation author="Koch, K." box="[774,1129,652,678]" page=")" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" year="1849">
<taxonomicName authority="Koch (1849: 228)" authorityName="Koch" authorityPageNumber="228" authorityYear="1849" box="[774,1129,652,678]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis box="[774,912,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. glacialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, K." box="[916,1129,652,678]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="226 - 231" refId="ref9432" refString="Koch, K. (1849) Beitrage zu einer Flora des Orientes (Fortsetzung): Gagea. Linnaea 22: 226 - 231." type="journal article" year="1849">Koch (1849: 228)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, 
<treatmentCitation author="Stapf, O." page=")" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" year="1885">
<taxonomicName authority="Stapf (1885: 80)" authorityName="Stapf" authorityPageNumber="80" authorityYear="1885" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luteoides">
<emphasis box="[1142,1281,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. luteoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stapf, O." pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="72 - 120" refId="ref10815" refString="Stapf, O. (1885) Beitrage zur Flora von Lycien, Carien und Mesopotamien. Planta collectaea Dre Felix Luschan ann. 1881, 1882, 1883, 1. Denkschriften der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Wien. Mathematisch- Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse. Vienna. 50: 72 - 120." type="journal article" year="1885">Stapf (1885: 80)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
and 
<treatmentCitation author="Levichev, I. G." box="[253,725,690,716]" page=")" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" year="2009">
<taxonomicName authority="Levichev (2009: 39)" authorityName="Levichev" authorityPageNumber="39" authorityYear="2009" box="[253,725,690,716]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microfistulosa">
<emphasis box="[253,463,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. microfistulosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Levichev, I. G." box="[473,725,690,716]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="39" refId="ref9697" refString="Levichev, I. G. (2009) New species of genus Gagea Salisb. (Liliaceae) from Crimean Yaila. Novitates systematicae plantarum vascularium, Moscow, St. Petersburg 40: 39." type="journal article" year="2009">Levichev (2009: 39)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
are the only species of this section that were included in molecular analyses using plastid and nrITS sequences (
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[826,1075,729,755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[941,1003,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1089,1307,729,755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1171,1233,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). They are classified as 
<emphasis box="[301,330,768,793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[395,548,768,793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Monophyllos</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[593,774,768,794]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">Pascher (1907)</bibRefCitation>
. Although they collectively form a clade in the analyses of plastid sequences, they were intermixed with 
<emphasis box="[739,765,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[836,1011,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
in analyses using nrITS sequences (
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[158,399,845,871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[269,328,845,870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). In analyses of combined datasets of plastid and nrITS sequences, these species formed a subclade with low bootstrap support (BP 73, Figure 
<quantity box="[796,842,884,910]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[850,1059,884,910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[930,990,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) within clade D. 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that, as well as some ontogenetic characters, the umbellate inflorescence plus terete seeds are common characters in the section. However, these characters are shared with several other sections such as 
<emphasis box="[1411,1436,961,986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[211,382,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,652,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">
Pollen characters do not support the distinctness of the section. The only species included in analyses conducted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." box="[324,595,1077,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre (2005)</bibRefCitation>
had the reticulate pollen 
<typeStatus box="[911,963,1077,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
shared with most members of 
<emphasis box="[1346,1372,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[151,322,1116,1141]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Pedicel anatomy supports the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bayer &amp; Lopez" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Vill." box="[860,999,1116,1141]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragifera">
<emphasis box="[860,999,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. fragifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a clade with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sweet" authorityYear="1826" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[1192,1305,1116,1141]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[1192,1305,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The basal leaf anatomy of this species was similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascher" authorityYear="1907" box="[765,944,1155,1180]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chomutovae">
<emphasis box="[765,944,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. chomutovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within clade D (Figure 
<quantity box="[1237,1283,1154,1180]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). In conclusion, 
<emphasis box="[435,461,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[539,671,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Fistulosae</emphasis>
should be reduced to lower taxonomic rank within 
<emphasis box="[1342,1368,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[151,322,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
(including all members of clade D, Figure 3, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[858,1066,1232,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[937,995,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
